docs.snippet: RIO DE JANEIRO, Feb. 27 -- In three whirlwind days in three Brazilian cities, President Eisenhower conquered this week a nation that emotionally awaited such conquest. The word "conquest" to describe the President's performance in Brazil is borrowed...
docs.lead_paragraph: RIO DE JANEIRO, Feb. 27 -- In three whirlwind days in three Brazilian cities, President Eisenhower conquered this week a nation that emotionally awaited such conquest. The word "conquest" to describe the President's performance in Brazil is borrowed from Brazilian newspaper editorial and headline writers who used it with conviction, unanimity and abundone throughout his stay in the country.
